# 3. 針は動き出す

Mafuyu: ...
Kanade: Do you need any help, Mafuyu? I'm free to lend you a hand.
Mafuyu: No, that's mostly everything. I didn't actually bring that many things over.
Mafuyu: I'll carry these down once my dad gets here.
Kanade: Okay...
Kanade: Things are going to feel quiet here without you.
Mafuyu: Huh?
Kanade: Oh, sorry... I'm happy that you're ready to go home now, Mafuyu.
Kanade: But I've also sort of gotten used to having you around.
Kanade: I'm a little sad that you're leaving.
Mafuyu: Kanade...
Mafuyu: I'll come back again from time to time.
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: Thank you...
Mafuyu: Because you might push yourself too hard and forget to eat again.
Kanade: Huh? N-No, I'll be fine. What I did was bad, and I've learned my lesson.
Mafuyu: If you don't eat properly, then I'm going to tell Mochizuki.
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: I-I'll be careful...
???: <Mafuyu, Kanade.>
Kanade: Miku, Len. We didn't see you there.
Len: <M-Mafuyu... We heard that you're going home today.>
Mafuyu: Yes, my dad should be here soon to pick me up.
Len: <Okay...>
Miku: <...>
Mafuyu: Is something wrong, Miku?
Miku: <Nothing's wrong...>
Miku: <I'm just a little worried is all.>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: I'm also a little anxious...
Mafuyu: But I'll be fine.
Mafuyu: I want to believe what my mom said.
Len: <Mafuyu...>
Miku: <Okay.>
Miku: <Good luck, Mafuyu.>
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Kanade: I hear a car coming. That must be your dad.
Kanade: Let's go, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Okay...
Mafuyu's Father: Alright, we're here. I'll carry your things for you.
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Mafuyu's Father: You can open the door when you feel ready, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: (Don't worry.)
Mafuyu: (You made the decision to believe in Mom.)
Mafuyu's Mother: Welcome home, Mafuyu!
Mafuyu: I'm back...
Mafuyu's Mother: Please, come in. Dinner is just about ready.
Mafuyu's Mother: Are you hungry?
Mafuyu: *Nod*
Mafuyu's Father: Oh, look at all the dishes on the dining table. We must be having a feast tonight.
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. I couldn't help it, since I knew Mafuyu was finally coming home.
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay, let's get your things settled and have dinner once everything is ready.
Mafuyu: Okay.
Mafuyu's Mother: So, once again... Welcome home, Mafuyu!
Mafuyu's Mother: Today's menu includes many of your favorite dishes. I made them just for you.
Mafuyu's Mother: I gave them some extra seasoning compared to normal. I hope you'll like them.
Mafuyu: Okay, thank you.
Mafuyu's Father: Everything looks delicious... I think I'll start with some of these cabbage rolls.
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. Those turned out very nicely.
Mafuyu's Mother: Let me know if you're not able to reach something, Mafuyu. I'll pass it to you.
Mafuyu: Umm...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, but there's just so much to choose from, isn't there?
Mafuyu's Mother: How about this? I was able to buy some very fresh snapper today, so I decided to sauté it. Give it a try.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, I'm sorry. Please choose whatever you like, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu's Father: I think we're all just excited about Mafuyu coming home.
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, I think so... I'll have to mind myself.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: Then, I'll have the snapper sauté.
Mafuyu's Mother: ...!
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay. I'll put it on your plate now.
Mafuyu: Thank you.
Mafuyu's Father: Anyway, since it's been so long, let's take this opportunity to catch up with each other.
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes! I'd love to hear about what you've been doing at school lately, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Okay, umm...
Mafuyu: (...)
Mafuyu: (I still can't taste anything...)
Mafuyu: (But...)
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. Still, Mafuyu, I had no idea that you helped put on a test of courage. I would've loved to see you at work.
Mafuyu's Father: Me too. I'm still having trouble picturing you as a cat monster, but I'm sure you looked very cute.
Mafuyu: (Even so, it feels warm.)
